In this article, President Trump addresses a group of United Nations Security Council ambassadors to discuss cooperation on various security challenges. These challenges include denuclearizing North Korea, countering Iran's destabilization activities in the Middle East, ending the Syrian conflict, and confronting terrorism. The President emphasizes the importance of the United Nations and the strength of its members. He also highlights the economic success of the United States and its positive impact on other countries. The ambassadors are shown Iranian missiles and arms transferred to militant allies in Yemen and later visit the Holocaust Museum to see atrocities in Syria. The President mentions the ongoing fight against the Taliban in Afghanistan, stating that there is no room for negotiations as they continue to commit atrocities and kill innocent people, particularly women and children. The President reiterates that the United States will finish what others have been unable to accomplish.